</disp-formula>The intuition is straightforward. Revenue sharing moves teams away from a noncooperative Nash equilibrium (defined by <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="disp-formula2-1527002512438616">Equation 2</xref>) toward a joint profit maximizing equilibrium (with equal sharing the objective of each team is identical to the objective of maximizing league profits). Joint profit maximization requires that the marginal revenue of a win is equalized across teams <inline-formula id="inline-formula1-1527002512438616">
