</inline-formula> so for the distribution of talent to be the same when there is less than equal sharing (the invariance principle) requires <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="disp-formula3-1527002512438616">Equation 3</xref> to be true at equilibrium.</p>
<p>Clearly then, the question is, under what circumstances does <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="disp-formula3-1527002512438616">Equation 3</xref> hold? FW do not examine any specific functional forms but instead refer the reader to their 2009 article in which they mention the generalized Tullock contest success function as:<disp-formula id="disp-formula4-1527002512438616">
