<p>Neither a strictly concave nor a strictly convex function <italic>h</italic>(.) will satisfy this condition with the exception of the trivial case where the marginal revenue functions are identical. For example, if <italic>h</italic>(.) is concave and <italic>z</italic>
<sub>1</sub> &gt; <italic>z</italic>
<sub>2,</sub> then both <italic>h</italic>(<italic>z</italic>
