<sub>2</sub>) and <italic>h</italic>′(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>1</sub>) &lt; <italic>h</italic>′(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>2</sub>), so that <italic>h</italic>(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>1</sub>) <italic>h</italic>′(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>2</sub>) &gt; <italic>h</italic>(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>2</sub>)<italic>h</italic>′(<italic>z</italic>
<sub>1</sub>). Generally, only an exponential function will satisfy <xref ref-type="disp-formula" rid="disp-formula3-1527002512438616">Equation 3</xref>, for example, <inline-formula id="inline-formula6-1527002512438616">
